### G. Seed DSL Compiler Pattern for Toposolids

**Location:** `/Users/jhoetter/repos/bim-ai/packages/cli/lib/seed-dsl.mjs` lines 218-273

```javascript
function compileToposolids(recipe) {
  const commands = [];
  for (const toposolid of recipe.toposolids ?? []) {
    const id = assertString(toposolid.id ?? toposolid.toposolidId, '$.toposolids[].id');
    // ... validation
    commands.push({
      type: 'CreateToposolid',
      toposolidId: id,
      name: toposolid.name ?? id,
      boundaryMm: assertFootprint(toposolid.boundaryMm, `$.toposolids.${id}.boundaryMm`),
      heightSamples: assertArray(...).map(assertHeightSample),
      heightmapGridMm?: assertHeightmapGrid(...),
      thicknessMm: number,
      baseElevationMm?: number,
      defaultMaterialKey: string | null,
    });

    // Also compile subdivisions (nested)
    for (const subdivision of toposolid.subdivisions ?? []) {
      commands.push({
        type: 'create_toposolid_subdivision',
        id: subdivisionId,
        hostToposolidId: id,
        boundaryMm: assertFootprint(...),
        finishCategory: 'paving' | 'lawn' | 'road' | 'planting' | 'other',
        materialKey: assertString(...),
      });
    }
  }
  return commands;
}
```

Each recipe field has a dedicated `compile*()` function that validates and transforms DSL to commands.

### H. Test Runner

**Vitest** is used throughout. Test configuration in `/Users/jhoetter/repos/bim-ai/packages/web/vite.config.ts`:
```typescript
